16/04/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Career diplomat Lazar Comanescu was sworn in on Tuesday (April 15th) as the country's new foreign minister.
He was nominated by Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu on Monday, following the resignation of Adrian Cioroianu.
After his swearing-in, Comanescu said that verifying the activities of Romanian embassies and consulates abroad will be a priority.
(Curierul national - 16/04/08;
Rompres, Mediafax - 15/04/08)
